-- MasterCard quarterly profit rises 10 pct
-- By Tanya Agrawal and Amrutha Gayathri
-- Thu Jul 31, 2014 08:05AM EDT
-- None



July 31 (Reuters) - MasterCard Inc <MA.N>, the world's second-largest debit and credit card company, posted a 10 percent rise in quarterly profit, as more customers used cards to make purchases.

The company's net income rose to $931 million, or 80 cents per share, in the second quarter ended June 30, from $848 million, or 70 cents per share, a year earlier.